



Gentlemen
In Council Feby 22d. 1781.



The object of the inclosed Memorial of Messrs. Stodder, Kerr and North being attainable by Congress only and proper to be the [690] subject of a representation from them I take the Liberty of transmitting it to you that Justice may be done to the parties interested.
I have the honor to be with great respect Gentlemen Your mo. ob. Hble Servant,

Th: Jefferson


P.S. We are and have long been without Letters of Marque.

